OL,3,C"I can't afford life": Council tax
OL,4,Crise piles pressure on cost of living
OL,6,FCouncil tax bills are set to increase
OL,7,Fon April 1st, as Citizens Advice warn
OL,8,Fthey are already giving 'crisis
OL,9,Fsupport' every 30 seconds for people
OL,10,Fstruggling with bills.
OL,12,FThe amount people pay for council tax
OL,13,Fwill rise on average by 4.9% in Wales.
OL,15,FHowever, that figure varies across the
OL,16,Fcountry. The highest increases are in
OL,17,Fthe Vale of Glamorgan and Conwy at
OL,18,F6.5% with the lowest at 3.5% in Neath
OL,19,FPort Talbot.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
