CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1774598700
OL,3,C"I can't afford life": Council tax
OL,4,Crise piles pressure on cost of living
OL,6,FSince devolution, in 1999, the Welsh
OL,7,FGovernment has had the powers to
OL,8,Fdetermine the funding formula for
OL,9,Fcouncil tax. However, it is down to
OL,10,Findividual local authorities to set
OL,11,Ftheir own levels and any annual
OL,12,Fincreases.
OL,14,FThe Welsh Government does have the
OL,15,Fability to set a cap on the maximum
OL,16,Fpercentage increase they can charge in
OL,17,Fa year, but they have never used this
OL,18,Fmechanism.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,465,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1774598700
OL,3,C"I can't afford life": Council tax
OL,4,Crise piles pressure on cost of living
OL,6,FEngland does have a cap, which means
OL,7,Fcouncil tax this year can only rise by
OL,8,Fa maximum of 4.99% unless a majority
OL,9,Fin a local referendum support the
OL,10,Frise, or the UK Government approves a
OL,11,Frequest which shows the council is
OL,12,Fsuffering significant financial
OL,13,Fdifficulties.
OL,15,FOver the last 27 years the annual
OL,16,Fpercentage increases in council tax
OL,17,Fhas been consistently higher in Wales
OL,18,Fcompared to England and Scotland.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
