OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1774598700
OL,3,C"I can't afford life": Council tax
OL,4,Crise piles pressure on cost of living
OL,6,F"Welsh Labour will always be prudent
OL,7,Fwith public money ` unlike Reform UK
OL,8,Fwho promise council tax cuts and then
OL,9,Fcan't deliver a single one. One Reform-
OL,10,Fled English council has raised council
OL,11,Ftax by almost 10%."
OL,13,FDan Thomas, the leader of Reform
OL,14,FWales, said: "Council tax in Wales is
OL,15,Frising at an alarming rate in some
OL,16,Fareas."
OL,18,F"These rises put real pressure on
OL,19,Fhousehold budgets, and often services
OL,20,Fdon't improve."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@SO]vD@NOUzD@AOU
